VYou are part of the maintenance crew aboard the //LGDE Heroism//, a colony ship bound for the 1212 Antilae system. Your team is responsible for bootstrapping the colony while the majority of the colonists stay in hibernation.\u000a\u000aSomething has gone incredibly wrong. When you awoke, the ship was not in the 1212 Antilae system, but orbiting a mysterious planet in an unknown binary star system. By some stroke of luck, the planet appears to be habitable. You finish with stasis recovery protocol in time to hear the news: the captain has given the order to begin colonization. Given the ship's limited fuel reserves and malfunctioning navigation system, he had no choice.\u000a\u000aYou stumble out of the recovery ward and into the maintenance lockers, where Captain Scott is giving a speech to the bustling crew. Some stand at attention, though the majority purposefully gather their gear and prepare to head to the planet.\u000a\u000a[[Listen to the captain's speech.|StartSlow]]\u000a\u000a[[Suit up.|StartFast]]
