VAt the far end of the ship is the drop pod hangar. Stacks of large pods (designed for moving colonists en masse) fill the room, leaving relatively little space to wander. <<if visited("Delay Pod")>>Most of the personal drop pods have launched already, but a few still remain. The pod in front of you looks just as good as any of them. <<else>>A few of the personal drop pods have launched already, but enough remain for you to take your pick. You inspect one of them, notice it is missing a large chunk of foam from the seat, and pick another. //Whoever gets stuck with that pod is in for a rough ride.//<<endif>>\u000a\u000aThese pods can only take you to the planet, not back. Once you launch you won't be able to return until the colonists awaken.\u000a\u000a[[Lets go.|Drop Pod]]\u000a\u000a[[I should double check my gear.|Delay Pod]]
