V<<if visited() is 1>>You walk up to the distinct, dome shaped structure that is the colony center. This structure is where the crew eats and sleeps, and in the future will be expanded to house the rest of the colonists. It could also be considered the colony's headquarters.\u000a\u000aLya is standing outside, waiting for you.\u000a\u000a//"Safe trip, I hope."// Lya begins. //"There's a lot to do, so I'll be brief. The colony's coming up a bit short on supplies, thanks to our detour. We're okay on food and prefabs but we're gonna run out of fuel soon. Do your job and survey what's around us, and keep an eye out for anything that might solve our energy problem."//\u000a\u000a[[//"Sounds good. Those mountains to the north are probably a good place to look."//|CCReply1]]\u000a\u000a<<if visited("Mountains") or visited("Forest") or visited("Hills") >>[[//"Already taken a look around. I'll have a report ready soon."//|CCReply2]]<<endif>><<else>><<if visited() is 2>>Lya nods. //"I'll be in touch via radio."// She heads into the dome shaped structure, leaving you alone. \u000a\u000a<<endif>>You stand outside of the colony center, a clean dome shaped structure which houses both crew quarters and the cafeteria. <<if $bio_lab < 2 and $spaceport < 2>>Lya, Dwayne and Inez are all inside, running the colony, keeping tabs on the crew's health, and watching the skies.<<elseif $bio_lab < 2>>Lya and Inez are inside, running the colony and keeping tabs on the crew's health.<<elseif $spareport < 2>>Lya and Dwayne are inside, running the colony and watching the sky.<<else>>Lya is inside, running the colony.<<endif>> \u000a\u000a<<if $weather_tower is 1>>Robots are hard at work in this area, building up a spire attached to the colony center. The tower seems to grow taller every time you blink.\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $weather_tower is 2>>A tall metal spire protudes from the dome, sampling the atomsphere. This weather tower will help the colony predict any inclement weather in the area.\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $comm_array is 1>>Robots are hard at work on the dome, running reinforced rods on the roof to support sensitive communications equipment. A pair of robots appear to be fine tuning the signal of the equipment, in preparation to send and receive signals from space. The uplink looks like it's coming together nicely.\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $comm_array is 2>> Large antennae stick out from the dome, supported by metal rods. These antennae enable two-way communication with the Heroism. <<if $jammer is 2>>In addition, a large satellite dish rests on top, pointed at the ominous island south of the colony, in an attempt to suppress it's signal.<<endif>>\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $jammer is 1>> Robots are hard at work modifying the communications antennae. It looks like they're tripling the number of antennae, as well as adding on a large dish, aimed at the ominous island south of the colony.\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $comm_array is 0>>When you have power to spare, let Lya know so she can work on rebuilding the communications array.\u000a\u000a[[//"Lya, go ahead and fix up your comms."//|Build Communications Array]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $comm_array is 2 and visited("Island") and $jammer is 0>>The signal that island is broadcasting definitely needs to stop. The robots should modify the comm system to jam that signal as soon as possible.\u000a\u000a[[//"Terra, send the robots to upgrade the comm system. I need it to jam the signal coming from the island to the south."//|Build Signal Jammer]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $visited_uncalm_ocean and $weather_tower is 0>>Not knowing the weather makes it difficult to travel on these alien waters. If the robots built a weather station here it would solve that problem. \u000a\u000a[[//"Terra, send the robots to build a weather station, please."//|Build Weather Tower]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>>When there's nothing left to do for today, you can sleep inside.\u000a\u000a[[Unwind and go to sleep.|Sleep]]\u000a\u000a<<if visited() is 2>>The path east leads back to the landing area and the center of the colony.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>[[Head east to the center of the colony.|Hub]]\u000a\u000a<<if visited() is 2>>The path west leads out of the colony, towards a wooded area full of alien looking trees.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>[[Leave the colony, heading west into the alien forest.|West of Colony]]<<endif>>
