V<<if visited() is 1>>You approach the colony's power plant, a set of tall unassuming prefabs which generate power for the day to day needs of the colony. Thick cables protrude from each building, connected to every other building in the colony.\u000a\u000aSoto, the power technician, is busily pacing from structure to structure, reading monitors and taking notes on his wrist screen. \u000a\u000a<<else>>You stand in front of the power plant for the colony.<<if $fuel>>The central prefab hums with power softly.<<endif>> <<if $aux_gen > 1>>On one side is the solar array, providing extra power to the colony.<<endif>> <<if $fusion_gen > 1>>On the other is the fusion reactor, humming with energy. <<endif>>Soto is here, <<if $generator > 2>>sitting back and relaxing.<<elseif $generator>>keeping a watchful eye on power levels.<<else>>frantically trying to balance power levels.<<endif>>\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $aux_gen is 1>>Robots are hard at work in this area, setting up arrays of mirrors and aligning them to a focal point to alleviate the colony's energy problems.\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $fusion_gen is 1>>Robots are hard at work in this area, constructing a strange spherical structure that you surmise will be a fusion reactor.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>You take a glance at the power plant's current status. <<if $fuel > 1>>There's enough fuel to run the generator for <<print $fuel>> days.<<elseif $fuel>>There's enough fuel to run the generator for the rest of today.<<else>>There's no fuel to run the generator.<<endif>> <<if $generator > 2>>The power plant has loads of capacity left.<<elseif $generator is 2>>The generator has some capacity left.<<elseif $generator>>The generator has a small amount of capacity left.<<else>>The generator is over capacity. Power rationing is in effect.<<endif>>\u000a\u000a<<if $aux_gen is 0>>The colony has an excess of solar mirrors. Using them to generate power would bolster the colony.\u000a\u000a[[//"Terra, send the robots to set up a solar farm at the power plant."//|Build Solar Farm]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $aux_gen is 2 and $refinery is 2 and $fusion_gen is 0>>Alloys produced by the smelter could be used to contain a fusion reaction. Fusion power should solve the colony's power needs.\u000a\u000a[[//"Terra, send the robots to build a fusion reactor at the power plant."//|Build Fusion Reactor]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $isotope>>The isotopes from the emitter can be used in the fusion reactor to generate fresh FTL fuel. With this fuel, the Heroism can leave the solar system.\u000a\u000a[[//"Soto, take these isotopes and refine them into FTL fuel."//|Refine Strange Isotope]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $mountain_mapped and $drill < 2>>The northern mountains hold hidden treasures that need to be dug up. You can charge your drill here.\u000a\u000a<<if $drill is 0>>[[//"Soto, can you charge my drill?"//|Charge Drill]]<<else>>[[//"Soto, can you overcharge my drill?"//|Charge Drill]]<<endif>>\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $beasts_known and $plasma_torch is 0>>The beasts around here are dangerous. You can overcharge your plasma torch to use as a defensive weapon here.\u000a\u000a[[//"Soto, can you overcharge my plasma torch?"//|Overcharge Plasma Torch]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if $bio_lab > 1>> [[Head south to the bio lab.|Bio Lab]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>><<if visited() is 1>>The path east leads out of the colony, toward the hills.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>[[Leave the colony, heading east toward the hills.|East of Colony]]\u000a\u000a<<if visited() is 1>> The path west leads back to the landing area and the center of the colony.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>[[Head west to the center of the colony|Hub]]
