V<<if $flight_suit > 1>>You climb down and pace the cave. Thick moss covers most of the walls. <<if $curious_plant is 0>>To one side, you notice a plant growing out of the wall with what appear to be strange looking growths along its stem.<<else>>There is nothing else of interest in this cave.<<endif>>\u000a\u000a<<if $curious_plant is 0>>You take a quick scan of the plant with your hand scanner. The plant itself is unknown, but the growths appear to be some other creature, parasitically attached to the plant. Even weirder, several of the growths contain human DNA.\u000a\u000aYou share your findings with the colony, and Lya's voice responds from the radio. //"Human DNA? That doesn't make any sense. What a bizarre finding. Try to bring the plant back with you, we'll want to study it.<<if $bio_lab is 0>> Oh, but we'll need a lab to study it. Inez. Inez? We've got a strange-- yes, yes. Talk with Terra, tell her what you need.<<endif>>"// \u000a\u000a<<set $curious_plant to 1>>You dig the plant out of the rock and put it in a glass container. The plant looks surprisingly hardy, it should be okay for a while.\u000a\u000a<<endif>>[[Climb back out.|Ocean Hills]]\u000a\u000a<<else>><<if $flight_suit is 0>><<set $need_flight_suit to 1>><<endif>>Unfortunately, the climb down is too steep for you. Surveyors normally used flight suits to get to hard to reach spots, but the ship didn't bring any. Lucy may be able to help you out.\u000a\u000a[[Okay.|Ocean Hills]]\u000a\u000a<<endif>>\u000a\u000a
