VThe pod launches <<if visited("Delay Pod")>>jerkily<<else>>gracefully<<endif>> from the Heroism, spinning around and giving you a clear view of the large blue planet you are about to descend towards. Autopilot thrusters press you into your seat, an uncomfortable reminder of the G-forces normally associated with atmospheric entry.\u000a\u000aYou squawk on the radio to the Heroism, //"Pod 126BB-M beginning  descent."//\u000a\u000aThe reinforced viewport starts to flare up as the pod rushes through atmosphere. The computer automatically closes the window, leaving you with only your instruments and trust in the autopilot. An eternity passes as the pod is endlessly jostled by atmospheric turbulence. Airfoils deploy and thrusters fire, and you feel the pod decelerating, the instruments showing the colony fast approaching. The landing goes like clockwork, with a gentle thud as the pod touches the ground and tips over.\u000a\u000aYou toggle the radio as it links in with the local Colony grid, //"Pod 126BB-M has landed safely. Getting out now."//\u000a\u000a[[Open the pod and step outside.|Hub]]
